<%# 2026-05-11 — Layout-level TOTP verification modal.

    The four settings panes that the fresh-TOTP gate guards — YouTube,
    Voyage.ai, Discord, Slack (the user-edit page has its own surface
    so it keeps the inline field for now) — used to render an inline
    `2FA code` text input above their `[update]` button. Per user
    direction 2026-05-11 the inline fields are gone; clicking
    `[update]` now opens this modal when `Current.user&.totp_enabled?`
    so the operator types the code into a Slack-style 6-box segmented
    input. Read-only submissions (2FA off) bypass the modal entirely
    and submit the form directly.

    Wiring:
      - Each gated `<form>` carries `data-controller="totp-modal"` and
        `data-action="submit->totp-modal#maybeIntercept"`.
      - On submit, the controller checks `data-totp-modal-required-value`
        on the form. When "yes", it preventDefault's the native submit,
        opens THIS dialog, focuses the first box, and waits for either
        `[confirm]` (writes the code into a hidden `totp_code` field
        inside the original form and re-submits) or `[cancel]` /
        backdrop / Esc (drops the dialog, form stays unsubmitted).
      - When "no", the submit passes through untouched.

    Segmented input UX:
      - 6 boxes, each `<input type="text" maxlength="1" inputmode="numeric"
        pattern="[0-9]*">`.
      - Typing a digit auto-advances focus to the next box.
      - Backspace on an empty box steps focus back; on a filled box,
        clears it in place.
      - Paste of a 6-char numeric string into ANY box fills all 6 from
        the left.
      - `[confirm]` (bracketed) submits; disabled until 6 digits typed.
      - `[cancel]` closes without submitting.

    No JS `confirm()` / `alert()` / `prompt()` / `data-turbo-confirm`
    (CLAUDE.md hard rule). The dialog IS the confirmation surface. %>
<dialog id="totp-verification-modal"
        class="confirm-modal totp-verification-modal"
        data-controller="totp-modal-dialog"
        data-action="click->totp-modal-dialog#clickOutside keydown->totp-modal-dialog#keydown">
  <div class="confirm-modal-inner">
    <div class="dialog-title">2FA code</div>
    <div class="dialog-message">enter the 6-digit code from your authenticator app.</div>

    <%# Six segmented input boxes. `data-totp-modal-dialog-target="box"`
        gives the Stimulus controller an indexed handle on each box;
        per-box `data-action` wires keydown / input / paste so paste
        from any box fills all six from the left. %>
    <div class="totp-modal-boxes">
      <% 6.times do |i| %>
        <input type="text"
               maxlength="1"
               inputmode="numeric"
               pattern="[0-9]*"
               autocomplete="one-time-code"
               aria-label="digit <%= i + 1 %>"
               class="totp-modal-box"
               data-totp-modal-dialog-target="box"
               data-action="input->totp-modal-dialog#onInput keydown->totp-modal-dialog#onKeydown paste->totp-modal-dialog#onPaste">
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <div class="modal-footer confirm-modal-actions">
      <button type="button"
              class="bracketed"
              data-totp-modal-dialog-target="confirm"
              data-action="totp-modal-dialog#confirm"
              disabled>[<span class="bl">confirm</span>]</button>
      <button type="button"
              class="bracketed"
              data-action="totp-modal-dialog#close">[<span class="bl">cancel</span>]</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</dialog>
